title: Suicide rate vs. death rate from violence (per 100,000)
subtitle: Age-standardized death rate from suicide, measured per 100,000 inviduals versus death rate from violence or murder, per 100,000. Deaths from violence include the categories of interpersonal violence (homicide), conflict and terrorism, and police conflict and executions. A line of parity (where suicide rate equals violent deaths rate) is also shown.
